{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Class Descriptions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 The Duelist\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A Duelist is a swashbuckling swordfighter who lives by her wits and her skill at her blade. She may be a member of the military, or may be a freelance fencer who runs her own dueling school. Quite a few actors have been known to take up dueling as well.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Duelist is appropriate to accompany any other class. As swordfighting is so prevalent in the game, the Duelist class is a natural choice for most appropriate character concepts.\line In other words, if you can\u8217't decide on a second class, choose Duelist.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Suggested Classes:} Any\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Suggested Passions:} Any\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Duelist Qualities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Skill Competency:} Dueling, Military, Streetwise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Specialties:} Defense (Parry +1, Dodge +1), Dueling (Lunge +1, Riposte +1, Feint +1), Streetwise (Banter +1)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Weapon Prowess:} Knife, Sword\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Armor Prowess:} Flexible, Shield\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Social Rank:} Soldier (D6)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Bonus Gear:} Swashbuckler outfit (cavalier hat, doublet, soldier\u8217's gloves, breeches, boots, cape), buckler (Shield +1D8), rapier (Sword +1D8)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Duelist Maneuvers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Confident Fencing:} Spend 1 Style Point to reroll a Dueling roll\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Deflecting Shield:} When using a Shield to parry, spend 1 Style Point to add Block dice to a Parry roll\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Last Resort:} Spend 1 Style Point to reroll a Defense roll\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Practiced Retort:} Spend 2 Style Points to set the value of one Riposte die to its maximum value before rolling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Precise Swordplay: }Spend 2 Style Points to set the value of one Sword weapon die to its maximum value before rolling\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 The Alchemist\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Alchemists brew potions, poisons, and antidotes based on scientific principles. They can produce a variety of effects, ranging from healing to magical abilities.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Most Alchemists are successful merchants, many running small apothecaries to vend their wares.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Suggested Classes:} Charlatan, Chirurgeon, Mechanician, Visionary, Witch\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Suggested Passions:} Artistry, Knowledge, Pride, Wealth\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Alchemist Qualities\par}
