{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Standard Opposition\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The total of your roll is the sum of the two dice you kept after rolling. The success points generated by your roll equal the lower of the two dice. If you beat the total of the opposition dice, then you can spend those success points on the success table for that specialty. Otherwise, your opponent can spend her success points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can usually buy a result from a success table multiple times, unless it says otherwise in the description of the specialty. Success points you don\u8217't use are simply discarded when you finish buying the results you want.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One of the most common ways to spend success points is to buy a style point for 3 success points. You use style points to power your style maneuvers, which let you combine together the Specialty Dice of two different specialties, set one die in a pool to its maximum value before you roll, or reroll a result that you don\u8217't like. You can only have 3 style points at a time, so if you already have 3, you can\u8217't buy any more.\par}
