{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Guile Specialty}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Deceive is the ability to tell a believable lie, avoiding telltale quirks and pitfalls that might reveal your duplicity. Lies which are obviously untrue and unbelievable impose a penalty of Drop 1 to Drop 4, at the Gamemaster\u8217's discretion.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Language:} If you and the other parties don\u8217't share a common language, you gain a Drop 4 penalty on all Interaction rolls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Time:} Deception rolls are made after each new, major claim is made, so could occur after 30 seconds of rambling, or hours of prolonged storytelling.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Knowledge Rolls:} This Specialty is not often used to make knowledge rolls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Crafting:} An alternate identity or a simple disguise, as described in Chapter 10, \u8220"Crafting.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Opposition:} Use the Intuition specialty of each person who is listening to the lies.\par}
