{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Supplies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Alchemical ingredients:} Chemicals, herbs, rare salts, parts of animals, and other materials used to create salves, draughts, poison, and medicine.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Art media:} Supplies for creating works of art, ranging from canvas and paints to sculpturing clay and marble blocks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Blackpowder charges:} Units of blackpowder that can create explosive weapons or be purified to produce phlogistone.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Clockwork gears:} The parts needed to create clockwork components that are then assembled into clockwork devices.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Crucible steel:} Worked metal that can used to make weapons, armor, clockwork gears, and more.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Fabric:} Cloth, lace, thread, silk, dyes, leather, buttons, and other materials for making clothing.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Foodstuffs:} Grains, fruit, meat, cheeses, sugar, eggs, bread, and other materials for cooking. One unit of uncrafted foodstuffs is enough to feed one person for one day.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Medicine:} Medicine, medicinal herbs, and other medical supplies used to treat injuries, cure diseases, create antidotes, and perform surgery.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Writing materials:} Paper and ink, used in creating reports, plans, and written works of art.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs16 Scrounging\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you have neither the necessary supplies on hand nor the ability to purchase more, you can spend your time scrounging \u8211- looking in refuse bins for art supplies, junk piles for crucible steel, discarded trimmings for fabric, or roadkill and old fruit for foodstuffs. Every two hours spent scrounging produces one unit of supplies \u8211- as long as your MJ agrees there are such supplies to be found. If you\u8217're lost in the middle of a frozen tundra, you probably can\u8217't find blackpowder charges just waiting for you to come along.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Tag Dice\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As described in Chapter 4, \u8220"Skills & Specialties\u8221", Tag Dice are a type of Bonus Dice that are tied to a specific concept. This could be a single word, an emotion, a Passion, a phrase, or other abstract constructions. The crafting description for each Specialty describes how each Tag is created, what you can associate each Tag with, and how you can increase the Bonus Die size of the Tag.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For example, if you create a painting of Bentheim Castle as seen from a grassy meadow, you could assign a Tag of \u8220"Peaceful.\u8221" The Tag Die starts at +1D0, and for every 2 success points, you can increase the size of that die. You can also use success points to add a different Tag, such as \u8220"Loyalty.\u8221" These additional dice also start at +1D0.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Tag Die can be added to a dice pool as a Bonus Die whenever it makes sense in the story \u8211- so if you\u8217're trying to calm down a visiting dignitary, you might seat her under the painting and add the Peaceful tag to your Interaction (Negotiate) dice pool. Alternately, if you\u8217're trying to inspire the soldiers of Bentheim Castle to stand firm and not desert in the face of the enemy, you may want to make your Interaction (Inspire) roll when you stand in front of the painting of the castle.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 Weapon Qualities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When you craft a weapon, it\u8217's assumed to be a \u8220"stock\u8221" version of that weapon as described in Chapter 8, \u8220"Equipment.\u8221" If you want to add something extra to a crafted weapon, you can add a Weapon Quality to that weapon. Each specialty\u8217's crafting description lists which qualities can be given to each type of weapon. The maximum number of Weapon Qualities you can add to any given weapon equals your rank in the crafting Specialty.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather than repeating the descriptions of Weapon Qualities in each crafting specialty, they\u8217're listed here for easy reference. You can\u8217't add the same Weapon Quality twice to a single weapon.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Cavalry:} A weapon with the Cavalry quality must be used with your Main Hand. If you are using this weapon while riding a mount, you can substitute the mount\u8217's Item Die for your Weapon Die against an unmounted opponent.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Defending:} You can use this weapon to make a Defense (Parry) roll and add the Weapon Die to your dice pool, even though this type of weapon usually can\u8217't be used for parrying.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Double-Barreled:} You can fire twice, once per barrel, without reloading. If you choose to fire both barrels in the same shot, the Weapon Die increases by one step, but you take a Drop 1 penalty because it\u8217's harder to aim. Reloading each barrel separately gives the normal Drop penalty for the unaltered weapon, and reloading both barrels is a Drop 4 combined action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Extended Long Range:} The weapon gains a Drop 2 penalty at Long range. This can only be applied to weapons which can\u8217't normally be used at Long range, but which can be used at Medium range.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Extended Medium Range:} The weapon gains a Drop 2 penalty at Medium range. This can only be applied to weapons which can\u8217't normally be used at Medium range.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b High-Caliber:} Increase the Weapon Die by one step. The Drop penalty for reloading the weapon increases by 1, and the Drop penalty at Long range increases by 2.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Lightened:} Decrease the Weapon Die by one step. If the unaltered weapon could be used in your main hand, you can now use it in either. If the weapon required two hands to use, it can now be used with just the main hand. You can\u8217't lighten a weapon that\u8217's been weighted.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Point Blank:} Decrease the Drop Penalty for Close range by 2.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Quickloading:} Decrease the Drop Penalty for reloading this weapon by 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Reach:} The weapon can be used to attack into an adjacent area as well as your own.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Responding:} The weapon can be used to make a Dueling (Riposte) roll and add the Weapon Die to your dice pool, even though this type of weapon usually can\u8217't be used for riposting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Rifled:} Reduce the Drop Penalty at Medium range by 1 and at Long range by 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Sparring:} You can use this weapon to make a Military (Brawl) roll and add the Weapon Die to your dice pool, even though weapons usually can\u8217't be used with Brawl.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Success Table: Specialty (Option)} You add an option for spending success points to a specific Success Table. The details for each option are described later in this section.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Throwable:} You can throw this weapon at a target using the Military (Aim) skill and add the Weapon Die to your dice pool, even though this type of weapon usually can\u8217't be thrown. The weapon has no Drop penalty at Close range, Drop 1 at Short range, and Drop 3 at Medium range.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Weighted:} Increase the Weapon Die by one step. If the weapon could be used in either hand, it now is only usable in your main hand. If the unaltered weapon required your main hand, it now requires both hands. You can\u8217't weight a weapon that\u8217's been lightened.\sa180\par}
