{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Buckler:} A buckler is a small shield that can be strapped to your forearm, usually on your non-dominant hand. You can hold an item in that hand but trying to attack with that hand while wearing a buckler gives you a Drop 2 penalty on rolls using either the buckler or that weapon.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Club:} A standard club is simply a piece of wood or metal that you can swing at someone. It\u8217's not very sophisticated, but then again, you can likely pick one up wherever you are at any given time.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Cutlass:} The favored weapon of buccaneers, pirates, and other sailors.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Dagger:} A dagger is a large knife that can also be thrown using the Aim specialty.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Quarterstaff:} A medium-sized pole wielded in both hands that can also be used in a Brawl dice pool as well.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Rapier:} The most common type of Sword is a sharp, pointy weapon that can be used for all types of fencing.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Sabre:} A lighter and faster weapon, the sabre is designed to be used from horseback although it functions equally well when dismounted.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Smallsword:} Effectively a smaller, lighter version of a rapier, a smallsword can be used in the same way \u8211- or you could dual-wield two of them if you want.\line \sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Uncommon dueling weapons have an availability of 1D0 in a capital city, 1D6 in any other city, and 1D8 in villages and other rural areas. The one exception is that a bullwhip always has an availability of 1D0.\par}
