{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs16 Powered Weapon\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A powered weapon is a melee weapon that has been modified with moving parts to make it even more deadly \u8211- for example, a rotating flail or a chain-toothed sword. The powered weapon component grants a bonus die that can be used whenever the device\u8217's Weapon Die is used, including Defense (Parry) rolls and Dueling rolls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Size Limit:} A device with the powered weapon component can be no larger than Portable size.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Requires Hand-to-Hand Weapon:} You can only add this component to a device if it already possesses the hand-to-hand weapon component. The powered weapon Bonus Die cannot exceed the Weapon Die of the device.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Table: Powered Weapon Component\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Space | Cost | Supplies | Power | Bonus Die |\line :\u8212-: | ;\u8211-: | :\u8212-\u8212-: | :\u8212-: | :\u8212-\u8212-\u8211-: |\line 1 | D6 | 1 gear | 1 | D6 |\line 1 | D8 | 2 gears | 1 | D8 |\line 2 | D10 | 3 gears | 2 | D10 |\line 4 | D12 | 4 gears | 3 | D12 |\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs16 Projectile Weapon\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A projectile weapon component fires a bullet, dart, arrow, quarrel, cannonball, or other projectile at a target. Most devices use the Military (Aim) specialty to attack, and gain a Weapon Die when doing so. As with other missile weapons in The Queen\u8217's Cavaliers, it\u8217's not necessary to track ammunition carried, but it is necessary to know whether or not the weapon is loaded.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In addition to selecting the Weapon Die, reload time, and range modifiers for the weapon, the designer also specifies which Weapon prowess is used with the weapon. Devices which require the Cannon weapon prowess use the Science (Blackpowder) specialty for attacks instead of Military (Aim).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Magazine:} A projectile weapon can optionally be fitted with a magazine component to increase the number of times it can be fired without reloading. In such a situation, the projectile weapon component loses its reload quality and uses the reload time of the magazine instead.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Size Limit:} A device with the projectile weapon component can be no larger than Carriage size. (For cannons on larger buildings or ships, just place the cannons as separate devices.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ranges:} The range of a projectile weapon component is determined by adding together a composite of all chosen range lines. Lines cannot be combined if they both contain a value for the same range. All ranges must be filled in with a Drop penalty or N/A.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The default ranges for a weapon with no extra space, cost, or power requirements are: close Drop 0, short Drop 0, medium Drop 1, long N/A.\par}
