{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 The Nine Laws of Fashion\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Charmwoven clothes are useful, stylish, and expensive, but they are also made according to exacting standards known as the Nine Laws of Fashion. Flouting these laws could lead to your Charms simply failing to work at all!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The First is the simplest Law:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 The First Law: The Law of Couture\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i \u8220"One\u8217's clothes must fit properly.\u8221"}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It seems obvious at first \u8211- clothing is meant to be worn and to fit properly! But it\u8217's also the most important. If your clothes aren\u8217't sized correctly for you, none of the charms will function. In addition, each off-size article of clothing you wear adds a Drop 1 penalty to combat actions if it\u8217's too large or too small.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To ensure your clothes are properly sized, you can\u8217't just buy your clothes off the rack; the people of France are a diverse group when it comes to body size, and there are no \u8220"standard sizes\u8221". Your clothes will need to be either be created specifically for you, or altered by a tailor. Only then can charms be effectively added to such apparel.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs20 The Second Law: The Law of Attunement\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i \u8220"Charms are unique to the wearer.\u8221"}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can\u8217't just pick up any random charmwoven item and put it on, even if it fits you. The patterns, glyphs, and trinkets sewn into charmwoven clothing have to be calibrated for each wearers. This is a pretty simple process \u8211- as long as the charmweaver knows your birth date, birth time, and place of birth. It usually takes about an hour to attune or reattune charms to any given person.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What if you don\u8217't know some or any of that information to tell your charmweaver? There are two options.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 First, your charmweaver can attempt to adjust the charms to you anyway, through trial and error. This takes one hour per piece of information about your birth that you\u8217're missing. At the end of that process, the charmweaver makes a simple Magicks (Weave) roll with the opposition pool based on how much they don\u8217't know, as shown on the following table.\par}
