{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Beret, Artisan\u8217's:} The simple woolen beret is common among crafters, and you can get a beret in many different colors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Capotain:} A capotain is a tall hat, usually flat on the top, with a narrow brim. Most capotains are black in color, and many sport buckles in front.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Cavalier Hat:} Cavalier hats have a wide brim and are usually worn with one side pinned up. A dyed ostrich feather is often added, both for appearance\u8217's sake and to allow all-black hats to take a charm.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Goggles, Gearspring:} These goggles are created and used by mechanicians as well as other crafters. Each set of goggles has two or more pairs of lenses that can be swapped in as necessary \u8211- functions include magnification of small objects, telescopic sighting of distant objects, filters for specific colors, or simple eye protection. Gearspring goggles offer a +1D6 Item Die on Observation (Perception) rolls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Hair Ribbons:} Magickally charmed hair ribbons are popular with the upper classes and are woven into the hairstyles \u8211- or wigs \u8211- of any gender of noble. Unless affixed to a wig (which must be one of the neutral colors of argent, brun\u226?tre, cendree, or sable), the ribbons require anywhere from ten minutes to several hours to weave into hair, or double that time if forced to don them without the help of a capable household servant.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Masque:} Not a bandanna clumsily worn by a common brigand to disguise her identity, a masque actually does little to hide one\u8217's appearance. Used by the nobility at their lavish parties, each is custom created to reflect the wearer\u8217's persona and opinions of herself. Many masques only encircle the eyes and the space between them, while others cover the entire face.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Plague Mask:} Part of a chirurgeon\u8217's standard surgical wear, a plague mask is usually styled like a bird\u8217's long beak, although other examples exist, such as long tusks or simply a cylinder. Goggles built into the mask provide covering for the chirurgeon\u8217's eyes, while medicinal herbs and complex filters in the \u8220"nose\u8221" cavity prevent infection of air-carried diseases.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Skullcap, Clerical:} Sometimes called calottes, these skullcaps are associated with clergy.\par}
